---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import FIRECalculatorBase from '../../components/calculator/FIRECalculatorBase.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Fat FIRE Calculator — Plan Your Luxury Early Retirement"
  description="Free Fat FIRE calculator for high earners who want to maintain their lifestyle in early retirement. Calculate your FIRE number using the 30x multiplier. Interactive charts and instant results."
  canonical="https://truefinancetools.com/fat-fire-calculator"
  ogImage="https://truefinancetools.com/og-fat-fire-calculator.png"
  ogImageAlt="Fat FIRE Calculator - Plan Your Luxury Early Retirement"
  pageType="article"
  keywords="fat fire calculator, fat fire number, luxury retirement, high income retirement, fire calculator 30x, fat fire strategy"
>
    <FIRECalculatorBase fireType="fat" />

    <section class="border-t border-hairline bg-canvas-soft py-16">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6">
        <h2 class="mb-8 text-center text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
          What is Fat FIRE?
        </h2>

        <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none text-body">
          <p class="mb-4">
            <strong>Fat FIRE</strong> is for high earners who want to maintain their current lifestyle in retirement. It requires <strong>30x your annual expenses</strong> saved — the most conservative multiplier among all FIRE strategies.
          </p>

          <p class="mb-4">
            Unlike Lean FIRE or Regular FIRE, Fat FIRE doesn't require lifestyle sacrifices. If you earn $200,000+ per year and want to keep spending at that level in retirement, Fat FIRE gives you the financial cushion to do so.
          </p>

          <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">The Fat FIRE Formula</h3>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-canvas-soft-2 p-4 font-mono text-sm text-ink">
            Fat FIRE Number = Annual Expenses × 30
          </div>

          <p class="mb-4">
            For example, if you spend $80,000 per year, your Fat FIRE number is $2,400,000. That's $400,000 more than Regular FIRE ($2,000,000) for the same expenses — but it provides a larger safety margin.
          </p>

          <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Who Should Choose Fat FIRE?</h3>
          <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">High Earners</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-body">Professionals earning $150K+ who want to maintain their lifestyle without compromise.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Families</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-body">Parents who need to cover children's education, healthcare, and family travel.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Healthcare Focus</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-body">Those who want premium healthcare coverage and don't want to rely on ACA subsidies.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Travel Enthusiasts</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-body">People who plan to travel extensively and need a larger budget for experiences.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-hairline bg-canvas py-16">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 text-center sm:px-6">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
          Explore Other FIRE Strategies
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-8 text-body">Compare different approaches to find the right one for your lifestyle.</p>

        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
          <a href="/lean-fire-calculator" class="group rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-5 text-left shadow-sm transition-all hover:shadow-md">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink group-hover:text-link">Lean FIRE Calculator</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-body">Minimalist approach with lower expenses.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/barista-fire-calculator" class="group rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-5 text-left shadow-sm transition-all hover:shadow-md">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink group-hover:text-link">Barista FIRE Calculator</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-body">Work part-time, let investments cover the rest.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
</PageLayout>
